    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers aswritten's tagline work — finalized lines, competing candidates, supersessions, and the style rules behind them. The mainline product tagline was [finalized 19 Mar after six iterations](narr:Claim_TaglineFinalized): a two-beat trust-then-proof structure, also captured as an [iteration-process note](narr:Obs_TaglineIterationProcess). Critique runs alongside: one child flags that [an earlier line named WHO not WHAT/WHY](narr:Obs_TaglineGap), and another insists [git-native is implementation detail, not customer value](narr:Obs_GitNativeNotTagline). Several candidate taglines coexist without a crowned winner — [\"The Demo IS the Delivery\"](narr:Obs_NarrativeAnchor_Tagline), [\"think like your org\"](narr:StyleObs_ThinkLikeYourOrg), the [\"reachability without interruptability\"](narr:StyleObs_ReachabilityPhrase) sales-motion coinage (21 Apr), and layered pitch language across [creation](narr:Obs_Tagline_Layer1), [architecture](narr:Obs_Tagline_Layer2), and [infrastructure](narr:Obs_Tagline_Layer3) differentiators. On 28 Apr the worldview's [\"The product is a phone number\" was explicitly superseded](narr:Claim_TaglineSupersession). Beneath sit dozens of style observations — lowercase brand stylization, em-dash cadence, all-caps \"IS\" refrains, rule-of-three — plus the [Elephant Collective \"dream bigger\"](narr:StyleObs_4) lineage of narrative-as-founder's-weapon.""" ;
